@mnieber Actually specifying the widget explicitly [shouldn't even be necessary](https://github.com/jonasundderwolf/django-image-cropping/blob/master/example/forms.py#L5).

Basically it's required that you include both relevant fields (the `ImageCropField` and the `ImageRatioField`) and make sure that the correct widgets are used (that they are not overriden, etc.).
The rest of the magic happens in the [`image-cropping.js`](https://github.com/jonasundderwolf/django-image-cropping/blob/master/image_cropping/static/image_cropping/image_cropping.js) (which is included by the widget): Here the `ImageRatioField`gets hidden and replaced the with cropping widget, etc.

