I went to investigate what this would take, and turns out it's surprisingly easy with a little bit of custom code.

```python

from marshmallow.utils import is_collection


class LookupNested(Nested):
    default_error_messages = {
        'type': 'Invalid input type. Expected a list.',
        'missing': 'Could not find related object {input}.',
    }

    def _deserialize(self, value, attr, data):
        if self.many and not is_collection(value):
            self.fail('type', input=value, type=value.__class__.__name__)
        instance = self.schema.get_instance(value)
        if not instance:
            self.fail('missing', input=value)
        return instance
```

This basically just overwrites `_deserialize` to call `get_instance(value)` on `ModelSchema` instead of doing a full load (which would attempt to create an instance).

