@JakubBrachTieto, thanks for submitting this PR.  I agree that changing the CPU clock configuration may be desirable for Thread Commissioning.  However, rather than having OpenThread dictate the clock configuration policy, I believe that policy should be left up to the platform.  

What OpenThread can do is provide greater visibility into the current state.  I propose that OpenThread invoke callbacks registered via [otSetStateChangedCallback](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/master/include/openthread/instance.h#L243) indicating `OT_CHANGED_COMMISSIONER_STATE` or `OT_CHANGED JOINER_STATE`.

